---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 17
  Paragraph: 54
Title: Autumn Floods
---
Chuang Tzu said, "Let's go back to your original question, please. You
asked me how I know what fish enjoy - so you already knew I knew it
when you asked the question. I know it by standing here beside the
Hao."
